The problem is already raised in [issue#22286][1], due to difference in autowire handling between Spring and Spring integration with JUnit. Which failed to do implicit autowire on constructor without `@Autowired`.

So as a workaround, add `onConstructor = @__(@Autowired)` to `@RequiredArgsConstructor` to annotate the generated constructor with `@Autowired`.

```java
@SpringBootTest
@RequiredArgsConstructor(onConstructor = @__(@Autowired))
public class B {
    private final A a;
...
}
```


